== stdout ==
Run the RGK restart-safe live Kaspa scanner

Usage: rgk-sync [OPTIONS] --url <URL> --db <PATH>

Options:
      --url <URL>
          Borsh wRPC endpoint, for example ws://127.0.0.1:18311/v2/kaspa/simnet/no-tls/wrpc/borsh [env: RGK_LIVE_KASPA_URL=]
      --network <NETWORK>
          Kaspa network/domain pair to use for the wRPC transport and RGK cursor domain [default: local-toccata] [possible values: mainnet, testnet, devnet, simnet, local-toccata]
      --db <PATH>
          Sled database directory for scan cursor and indexed RGK state [env: RGK_SYNC_DB=]
      --cursor-name <NAME>
          Named scanner cursor to load and update
      --min-confirmations <COUNT>
          Minimum virtual-chain confirmation count for scanned blocks
      --once
          Run exactly one scanner tick, then flush and exit
      --forever
          Keep polling until Ctrl+C
      --max-idle-ticks <MAX_IDLE_TICKS>
          Stop finite mode after this many consecutive idle ticks [default: 1]
      --poll-ms <POLL_MS>
          Poll delay for forever mode after an idle tick [default: 1000]
  -h, --help
          Print help

